The paper discusses a method for building a hypertextual network to aid navigation in a document, which involves selecting descriptors, identifying relevant text segments, and ranking them by relevance. This involves natural language processing techniques such as document segmentation and information ranking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper also involves techniques such as text classification and relevance ranking, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
